===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''pivot'', probably connected with [[w:Italian language|Italian]] ''[[pivolo]]'', "peg, pin", diminutive of ''[[piva]]'', ''[[pipa]]'', "pipe").

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/&#x02C8;p&#x026A;v&#x0259;t/}}

===Noun===
'''pivot'''  (''plural:'' '''[[pivots]]''')
# A '''pivot''' is that on which something turns; specifically a [[metal]] [[point]]ed [[pin]] or short [[shaft]] in [[machinery]], such as the end of an [[axle]] or [[spindle]].
# Act of turning on one foot
